<dl id="n05035i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05035i">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05035i"> 35(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> passage = death</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">One year, when the Festival of the Saint&apos;s <mark>&lsquo;Passage&rsquo; (or passing into eternity)</mark> fell on a Saturday, he appeared to the seven at the hour of the Sunday matins. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 72</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02035b" href="c02all.htm#c02035b">VI.C.02:035(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
